ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course. A great way to hone programming and math skills simultaneously.
It is very useful. Yes, definitely I will.
A really good course for students doing computation or data analysis.Yes, absolutely. They will really learn something useful and not easily lost.
Yes, I would recommend this course to a fellow student as it would teach important numerical methods in a rigorous fashion.

ENAS 747 01 is an introductory class in Numerical Methods. It deals with some of the main topics in Numerical Methods (root finding, linear systems, integration, interpolation). I would surely recommend this course to another student. The subjects are explored in depth and in a very clear manner, and the homework assignments ensure also the acquirement of a practice knowledge of the methods.
Sure, I will recommend this class to other students whose major is related to math calculation. It will pave the way for your future research to some degree.
I would recommend this class for students wanting to learn how to write programs, but I would let them know its a hard course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It is good supplement dealing with complicated equations that I dealed with in other courses. I could use the programs in the homework to figure out the answers to these equations.I
The course gave me an good introduction to computation and coding. It helps me a lot with my research.

Numerical Methods are routinely used in my research, and sometimes in the past I maybe used them without having an appropriate knowledge. This course gave me many instruments to evaluate a method and to understand its eventual limitations.
Itdeepens my knowledge of discipline mainly by providing me with the numerical thought to handle my research data.
This course helped me learn a how to program in matlab, which will be useful for producing models.
